    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-11T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-11T02:00:00-05:00" n="249"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">330/10–1151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Pakistan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Karachi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-11T12:00:00+05:00"
                            >October 11, 1951—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>384. Ref <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 379 10th Oct 11 a. m. Fol my
                    conversation with <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss>, Assoc Press <gloss
                        target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> yesterday carried govt-sponsored note that
                    people of <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> disappointed failure <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> discuss Kashmir issue since return of Graham to
                    NY end last month.</p>
                <p>Today English-language press carries protest by several named leaders Muslim
                    League, single party supporting govt, protesting failure <gloss target="#t_Pak1"
                        >Pak</gloss> Govt’s “wait and see fon policy”. Press also carried today note
                    all student bodies in Karachi colleges and univs held mtgs yesterday to organize
                    campaign for action on Kashmir. <hi rend="italic">Civil and Military
                        Gazette</hi>, in leading editorial (ref <gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">en clair</hi> 383 Oct 11),<note n="1" xml:id="d249fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> advocates popular demonstrations as most effective means to
                    attract internatl attn to problem and cites its effectiveness in Iran and Egypt.
                    If <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> Govt promotes or even permits renaissance
                    of popular emotion to attract internatl attn to Kashmir issue at this time I
                    believe it invites an uncalculated risk of war. At the same time there is
                    justification for impatience shld <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> fail to take
                    up Graham report without further delay. I urge strongly that US and UK support
                    hearing on Graham report within the next week and so forestall the extension to
                        <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss>s [of] a chain reaction against UK that
                    might easily affect dissident elements in this country.</p>
                <p>Dept pass <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
